7:37:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491901\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179987\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542902245\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154640\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Rocket In My Pocket\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Rocket In My Pocket said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat mod adds the names to the sides? That\u0027s actually pretty cool.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPretty sure this is the one I use.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed2939332640\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/154127-131-14-15-nebula-space-engineering-decals-continued/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:228px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EdwardB3020","CreatedById":223607,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-22T18:39:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpace Shuttle names anyone?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also lost a wing on landing \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022PnbUN53.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/PnbUN53.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022jRsyGDH.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/jRsyGDH.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022RuHLtfG.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/RuHLtfG.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022HhcaPJ0.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/HhcaPJ0.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022kKuXfra.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022640\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/kKuXfra.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://drive.google.com/file/d/1mUHvdyIJpLIHZEvKBwy-eQ5t03lLwJxj/view?usp=sharing\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://drive.google.com/file/d/1mUHvdyIJpLIHZEvKBwy-eQ5t03lLwJxj/view?usp=sharing\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSaturn Tanker Download. All crafts are for KSP 1.5.1 and with Making History\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"I_Killed_Jeb","CreatedById":84817,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-24T05:11:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223491923\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179987\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221542905171\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022176465\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Trekkie148\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 11/22/2018 at 8:46 AM, Trekkie148 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy shuttle in orbit\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh yeah I had to bring a tanker up to de fuel it a little\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhy the radiators?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"SiriusRocketry","CreatedById":178125,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-24T06:26:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have this problem too- my shuttle flips when the OMS turns on. It\u0027s your basic 3 Vector and two Thud deal, but when the Vectors go off and the top mounted Thuds ignite, the craft pitches down like crazy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"MR L A","CreatedById":150940,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-24T14:52:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/176465-trekkie148/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022176465\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/176465-trekkie148/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Trekkie148\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0was that screenshot (the one in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003Esph\u003C/abbr\u003E with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E) fuelled or unfuelled? If it was fuelled then that\u0027s probably your issue... when the tank empties that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E is going to shoot backwards...\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/178125-siriusrocketry/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022178125\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/178125-siriusrocketry/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SiriusRocketry\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0sounds like you need to realign your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EdwardB3020","CreatedById":223607,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-24T15:12:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223492852\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179987\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221543071147\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150940\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022MR L A\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, MR L A said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/176465-trekkie148/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022176465\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/176465-trekkie148/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Trekkie148\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0was that screenshot (the one in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003Esph\u003C/abbr\u003E with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Lift\u0022\u003ECoL\u003C/abbr\u003E) fuelled or unfuelled? If it was fuelled then that\u0027s probably your issue... when the tank empties that \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E is going to shoot backwards...\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/178125-siriusrocketry/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022178125\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/178125-siriusrocketry/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@SiriusRocketry\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0sounds like you need to realign your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe one in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022SpacePlane Hangar\u0022\u003Esph\u003C/abbr\u003E was unfuelled\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-24T15:27:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223492722\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179987\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221543040801\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022178125\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022SiriusRocketry\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, SiriusRocketry said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI have this problem too- my shuttle flips when the OMS turns on. It\u0027s your basic 3 Vector and two Thud deal, but when the Vectors go off and the top mounted Thuds ignite, the craft pitches down like crazy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E, turn your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E on.\u00A0 Turn the thrust limited on the vectors down to zero.\u00A0 The \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E indicator doesn\u0027t care about what\u0027s in what stage.\u00A0 Then you can try to line it up with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFirst pic is with Vectors at 100, second is with them at 0.\u00A0 Obviously, in flight, you\u0027ll simply have them turned off, but for the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E, they need to be set at zero thrust.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002244escreenshot16.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022609\u0022 src=\u0022http://u.cubeupload.com/Geonovast/44escreenshot16.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022caascreenshot17.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022609\u0022 src=\u0022http://u.cubeupload.com/Geonovast/caascreenshot17.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s not perfect, but it\u0027s better.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou won\u0027t get it perfect, it never can be.\u00A0 Your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E will move around with the payload and fuel consumption, so it\u0027ll take some practice to find a balance.\u00A0 It\u0027s especially tricky since the gimble overreacts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou\u0027ll also want an alternative control point in that line, otherwise you\u0027ll still have issues with the manuever node / prograde / whatever indicators not lining up with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI stick a jr docking port between the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E indicators.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022a36screenshot18.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022609\u0022 src=\u0022http://u.cubeupload.com/Geonovast/a36screenshot18.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWith the offset tool in local mode, you can see where \u0022forward\u0022 (green arrow) will be when using the docking port as your control point.\u00A0 You want that lined up best you can with your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00224e5screenshot20.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022609\u0022 src=\u0022http://u.cubeupload.com/Geonovast/4e5screenshot20.png\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf \u0022forward\u0022, \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E are lined up, you won\u0027t be flipping.\u00A0 It\u0027s not important which way the cockpit is facing when you\u0027re in space.\u00A0 Even if your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E and \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E are lined up, if they\u0027re not lined up with your control point, it will try to gimble to get your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E lined up with your control point, pointing it away from the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, causing flipping.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-24T20:31:48Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese questions about how to play the game have been moved to Gameplay Questions.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"bewing","CreatedById":154251,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-24T21:14:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the problem is more likely to be that the pitch control surfaces are pretty much inline with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, so the plane has no pitch control authority. So it\u0027s going to be unstable in pitch no matter what you do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EdwardB3020","CreatedById":223607,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T00:19:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223493036\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179987\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221543094063\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154251\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022bewing\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, bewing said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think the problem is more likely to be that the pitch control surfaces are pretty much inline with the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, so the plane has no pitch control authority. So it\u0027s going to be unstable in pitch no matter what you do.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I would need a separate canard not at the Center of Mass that has pitch. maybe something like this?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022013.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022536\u0022 src=\u0022http://www.collectspace.com/images/news-031510a/013.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GRYPHUS-01","CreatedById":166165,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T06:13:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, in order to make a succesfull space shuttle, you indeed need to build the shuttle in\u00A0 your expected \u0022Re-entry\u0022 state =\u0026gt; the state in which the space shuttle will get back into the atmosphere. this is the start for balancing your shuttle out for descend and final flight to \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Space Center\u0022\u003EKSC\u003C/abbr\u003E. Next is adding the OMS engines. To balance these properly out you need to put all your tanks at half weight and see where the Center of Mass ends up to. once you have its location its just a matter of placing engines symmetric with their \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E aiming through the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E. (!!!! Make sure that if you have attached the main engines for ascend, to turn the thrust limiter to \u00220\u0022. Otherwise your indicated \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E line will include the projected thrust from those engines, whilest in reality when in orbit, those engines are dead. This will throw your entire balancing off, causing instabilty. once that is done. you need to continue to build the shuttle up to its final shape, with all weight included ( engines, boosters everything), again turn the thrust limiter of the OMS engines to 0 for the same reason as earlier. Then detach the Boosters to exclude their weight from the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, put the weight of the main tank in half again, line the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E of the main engines up and then put the booster back on their place. this might seem to set the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Thrust\u0022\u003ECoT\u003C/abbr\u003E line under the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E, but the tiny gimbal range will counteract it on the launch. and while the weight lowers, the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E will drop too, stabilizing it even more.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve managed to build a stable stock space shuttle like this. but i went on to mods for aesthethics and functionality like robo arms etc.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt all a matter of simulating all states of your shuttle and checking the balance out for each state.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nA few pics of my old stock shuttle and the newer ones:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022C774C3A8742A4610E1DE55E92A03ACCD9902D053\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/480019269559033787/C774C3A8742A4610E1DE55E92A03ACCD9902D053/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002220043FC7D9B767A548FD25064903735C679D1DF8\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/480019269558490522/20043FC7D9B767A548FD25064903735C679D1DF8/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022631E3B0823E43C1F3426158FD7EE14DC83038C3F\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/480019269559034522/631E3B0823E43C1F3426158FD7EE14DC83038C3F/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002250072E51E01802A2E375A8F70D3C7196699751D2\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/942810750075924716/50072E51E01802A2E375A8F70D3C7196699751D2/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022DD3C4B2A0FB97C7B1C3CD014C8890F6A4CEB8B2D\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/942810750075924425/DD3C4B2A0FB97C7B1C3CD014C8890F6A4CEB8B2D/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd With my current Mods: \u003Cimg alt=\u00227D002F20B9217F6DD683D476AB5B06E1F48736CF\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/964230166658924992/7D002F20B9217F6DD683D476AB5B06E1F48736CF/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-11-25T06:22:55Z\u0022 title=\u002211/25/2018 06:22  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003ENovember 25, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by GRYPHUS-01\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EResized Images\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GRYPHUS-01","CreatedById":166165,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T06:33:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u002285052D7ABAB74FF1804200E98D291CDFB95DD898\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/964230166659074493/85052D7ABAB74FF1804200E98D291CDFB95DD898/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u00222F07F3B860926A28F2EE9873627F9EEE4AA1FFCB\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022576\u0022 src=\u0022https://steamuserimages-a.akamaihd.net/ugc/964230166659074340/2F07F3B860926A28F2EE9873627F9EEE4AA1FFCB/\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"michal.don","CreatedById":150623,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T12:17:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, if you want some inspiration, there happen to be plenty of awesome shuttle designs in \u0022my\u0022 STS challenge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5959461543\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/164104-shuttle-challenge-v5-the-sts-thread-stock-and-mod-friendly-new-mission-2192018-new-test-pilot-mission-19102018/\u0026amp;\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(A bit of a shameless plug, I admit \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u00A0)\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EBut feel free to browse the entries a bit, and maybe even fly a mission or two, we have a small but passionate shuttle community over there \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cspan\u003EMichal.don\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EdwardB3020","CreatedById":223607,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-11-25T13:27:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223493342\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179987\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221543148269\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022150623\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022michal.don\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, michal.don said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso, if you want some inspiration, there happen to be plenty of awesome shuttle designs in \u0022my\u0022 STS challenge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1079256071\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/164104-shuttle-challenge-v5-the-sts-thread-stock-and-mod-friendly-new-mission-2192018-new-test-pilot-mission-19102018/\u0026amp;\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:222px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(A b